\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish a consistent,
 auditable framework for the designation,
 governance,
 execution,
 and closure of IT projects within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 This policy defines what constitutes a formal IT project,
 governs the full project lifecycle from charter through post-mortem,
 and ensures that project work is authorized,
 documented,
 and delivered in alignment with the Department's governance obligations and service commitments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
In Scope
\series default
:
 This policy governs all initiatives formally designated as IT projects by the Information Operations Department,
 including new system implementations,
 major infrastructure changes,
 county-wide technology rollouts,
 departmental pilots,
 and multi-stakeholder technology initiatives managed by the Department.
 Both internal projects —
 those originated by the Information Operations Department to fulfill its own operational,
 infrastructure,
 or governance objectives —
 and external projects —
 those initiated by a County department,
 agency,
 or external entity where the Department participates as a technical authority and service partner —
 are governed by this policy.
\end_layout

