\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Project Designation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
An initiative qualifies for formal project designation when it (a) requires three or more discrete work orders to complete,
 and (b) requires advance resource planning,
 stakeholder coordination,
 or sequenced task dependencies that cannot be captured within a single work order record.
 Both conditions shall be satisfied for threshold-based designation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director or IT Director may designate any initiative as a formal project regardless of whether it meets the threshold criteria.
 No initiative may self-designate as a project below the threshold without authorization from the Assistant IT Director or IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Emergency Designation
\series default
:
 An initiative may be formally designated as a project after work has already begun when urgency precludes advance charter preparation —
 for example,
 a county-mandated security remediation requiring an immediate multi-work-order response.
 Emergency designation requires IT Director authorization.
 Catch-up documentation,
 including the project charter,
 risk log,
 stakeholder map,
 and all other required project record elements defined in Section 6.10,
 shall be completed and attached to the master work order within five business days of emergency designation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Project Record Structure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Each formally designated project shall be represented in Redmine as a master work order,
 which serves as the project record and coordination hub.
 The master work order shall have the Internal Project checkbox set per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and 
work order operational standards maintained in the System of Engagement
.
 Individual task units shall be created as child work orders and linked to the master via the Related Issues field.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Post-Implementation Review (PIR) fires on any Significant or Emergency change within a child work order per the timelines and mechanics established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This is a change-level obligation that runs independently of this policy.
 A separate project post-mortem under Section 6.7 fires when the master work order closes,
 covering the initiative as a whole.
 These two obligations are parallel and distinct.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Phase 1 —
 Initiation and Charter
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Project Owner shall define the project scope,
 objectives,
 impacted stakeholders,
 resource requirements,
 success criteria,
 and target completion date.
 The charter shall explicitly document:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Whether the project is net-new-service-bearing,
 for purposes of the service catalog closure gate in Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Whether the project involves vendor engagement,
 which triggers the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 SCRM gate before contracts are executed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Whether the project involves systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit County data,
 which flags the data classification obligation in Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall approve the charter before any project work begins.
 The master work order shall be created in Redmine upon charter approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
For emergency project designations,
 IT Director authorization substitutes for advance charter approval.
 Catch-up documentation shall be completed within five business days of emergency designation per Section 6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Phase 2 —
 Planning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
