\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.9 Project Cancellation,
 Suspension,
 and IT Withdrawal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Internal Projects
\series default
:
 Formal cancellation or suspension of an internal project requires IT Director authorization.
 All in-flight child work orders shall be closed or suspended with their current state documented.
 CMDB and KB entries shall be updated to reflect completed work.
 No obligation exists to revert partially-configured systems to their pre-project baseline.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
External Projects —
 Agreed Closure
\series default
:
 IT's role in an external project may be formally closed when the IT Director and all project sponsors concur that IT's role is complete.
 IT's role may be formally closed while the project continues under the sponsor's direction.
 Upon formal closure of IT's involvement,
 the Information Operations Department carries no further obligation for the project's outcomes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
External Projects —
 IT Withdrawal Over Objection
\series default
:
 The IT Director and Assistant IT Director may jointly declare a formal IT withdrawal from an external project when continued involvement is technically,
 financially,
 or operationally untenable —
 for example,
 when scope changes imposed by external parties conflict with the Department's security,
 architecture,
 or resource obligations,
 or when the project direction creates unacceptable risk to County systems or ongoing service commitments.
 Neither the IT Director nor the Assistant IT Director may invoke withdrawal unilaterally.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Prior to withdrawal,
 the County Manager shall be notified in writing of the basis for the Department's position.
 The County Manager may,
 at her option,
 serve as a neutral arbitrator between the sponsoring agency and the Information Operations Department to ensure good-faith resolution before withdrawal is finalized,
 consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 If the County Manager's arbitration does not resolve the impasse,
 the IT Director and Assistant IT Director may proceed with withdrawal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Upon withdrawal,
 the Project Owner and County Manager shall receive written notice documenting the basis for withdrawal and the current state of all IT work.
 All in-flight IT work orders shall be closed or suspended with their current state documented.
 CMDB and KB entries shall be updated to reflect completed work.
 No obligation exists to revert partially-configured systems to their pre-project baseline.
 The project may continue under the sponsor's direction;
 the Information Operations Department carries no further obligation for its outcomes.
\end_layout

